So, now you know moreover
why we brought you here.

32:38.057 --> 32:40.657
-We need your horsepower
more than your brainpower.
-Yeah, I got you.

32:40.659 --> 32:42.059
You know, daniel
is several years

32:42.061 --> 32:43.160
younger than me and digger.

32:43.162 --> 32:45.996
You can look at him,
he's stout as a bear.

32:45.998 --> 32:47.030
[digger] once you
get it going,

32:47.032 --> 32:48.532
it will come out on its own.

32:48.534 --> 32:49.766
<i> [ramsey] these</i>
<i>  barrels are full,</i>

32:49.768 --> 32:51.568
they're heavy,
600 pounds each.

32:51.570 --> 32:53.370
Watch your fingers,
watch your fingers, boys.

32:53.772 --> 32:54.705
[grunts]

32:54.707 --> 32:57.474
you know, you can't
have too much help.

32:57.476 --> 33:00.143
[digger] I hope we got enough
juice to get it up there now.

33:00.145 --> 33:01.244
That's a heavy bastard,

33:01.246 --> 33:03.246
did you hear the truck
squeak right down there?

33:03.248 --> 33:05.415
[ramsey] you can kick it,
how you go, hatty.

33:05.417 --> 33:07.851
How about them apples,
huh, mister?

33:07.853 --> 33:09.653
I just don't wanna
drop it too fast.

33:09.655 --> 33:11.822
[grunts]
I hope this old deck's solid.

33:11.824 --> 33:14.124
If we can get it on
wood, it will help us.

33:14.126 --> 33:15.359
[daniel] there, we got one.

33:15.361 --> 33:17.227
-Damn!
-[digger] just take your time.

33:17.930 --> 33:18.996
[sighs]

33:18.998 --> 33:21.098
[ramsey] all right,
it's good enough.

33:23.102 --> 33:25.068
[digger] we've got ten
barrels with us.

33:25.070 --> 33:27.738
That's what tennessee whisky,
we've got cup.

33:27.740 --> 33:29.906
Son of a bitch, this is too
much like work, boys.

33:29.908 --> 33:32.009
And if we can get them
in some of these seats

33:32.011 --> 33:34.144
<i>  and get 'em moving,</i>
<i> we're going to be in business.</i>

33:34.146 --> 33:36.346
-[daniel] we got it.
-Put it right there now.

33:39.018 --> 33:40.283
Hard on fat boys, ain't it.

33:40.285 --> 33:41.952
[ramsey laughs]
yup.

33:41.954 --> 33:44.354
We got to get that damn
cherry picker up here.

33:45.024 --> 33:46.156
Damn you.

33:47.192 --> 33:49.059
[all exclaiming]

33:49.328 --> 33:50.360
[ramsey] here you go.

33:50.396 --> 33:51.928
[digger] 30-40 more minutes
of that and I'd have

33:51.930 --> 33:53.930
this thing jacked up high
enough to get her on there.

33:53.932 --> 33:55.665
[ramsey] oh, it's,
just a little tedious

33:55.667 --> 33:56.833
but sure will help.

33:56.835 --> 33:58.935
Put it right there.
Hold it right there.

33:59.371 --> 34:00.337
[daniel] look at it.

34:00.339 --> 34:02.139
<i> [ramsey] you know,</i>
<i>  we gotta secure 'em.</i>

34:02.141 --> 34:03.306
We don't wanna
come back up here

34:03.308 --> 34:04.708
and them fell
through the deck,

34:04.710 --> 34:06.443
<i>  laying on the ground,</i>
<i>  busted open.</i>

34:06.445 --> 34:08.445
And all our liquor running
down buck mountain.

34:09.214 --> 34:10.881
[digger] oh, we're good.

34:10.883 --> 34:12.816
[ramsey] that right there is
the motion of the ocean, boys.

34:12.818 --> 34:14.184
It is.

34:14.186 --> 34:16.586
If it just moves around like
this here during some wind,

34:17.189 --> 34:17.921
that's plenty.

34:17.923 --> 34:19.156
It sure is.

34:19.158 --> 34:20.390
You know, when you
look at these things,

34:20.392 --> 34:22.826
it kinda looks like, a baby
sitting in a cradle.

34:22.828 --> 34:25.195
<i>  It's kinda what it is.</i>
<i>  It's in infant stages,</i>

34:25.197 --> 34:27.030
now we gotta
bring it to maturity.

34:28.333 --> 34:29.299
A-ha.

34:29.301 --> 34:31.034
I guess that's the end of it,
boys.

34:31.036 --> 34:32.369
<i> Do we bring some more up here?</i>

34:32.371 --> 34:35.005
<i> [ramsey] now, we're</i>
<i>  gonna start building sails.</i>

34:37.242 --> 34:39.476
<i> [digger] well, mark has</i>
<i>  come up with a design,</i>

34:39.478 --> 34:41.478
we're gonna build
kind of a square

34:41.480 --> 34:43.547
<i>  and tack a tarp to it.</i>

34:46.085 --> 34:47.784
<i>  Then, we're gonna screw that</i>

34:47.786 --> 34:49.219
to the ride itself.

34:50.823 --> 34:52.989
[daniel] hell, yes, I got
my raise, boys.

34:52.991 --> 34:54.424
[ramsey] hell,
if this is that,

34:54.426 --> 34:56.393
-we'll make
a move to the next.
-[daniel] move on.

35:03.936 --> 35:05.102
Well, it's gotten cooler.

35:05.104 --> 35:07.237
We can hear thunder
in the distance.

35:07.239 --> 35:09.739
<i>  We might just very well</i>
<i>  see a little bit of wind</i>

35:09.741 --> 35:10.941
<i>  come here in a little bit.</i>

35:10.943 --> 35:12.242
<i> [ramsey] you know,</i>
<i>  we spent a lot of time</i>

35:12.244 --> 35:13.910
<i>  trying to build</i>
<i>  this contraption.</i>

35:13.912 --> 35:16.079
We're betting it all,
we're letting the big end drag

35:16.081 --> 35:17.414
on this adventure here.

35:17.416 --> 35:19.916
It doesn't take a rocket
scientist to figure out

35:19.918 --> 35:21.685
<i>  that we're kinda</i>
<i>  deeply invested</i>

35:21.687 --> 35:23.286
<i>  in this tennessee whisky,</i>

35:23.288 --> 35:26.756
<i>  so we got no choice but</i>
<i>  to get these barrels to move.</i>

35:26.758 --> 35:29.292
-I know one thing, boys.
-[daniel] what's that?

35:29.294 --> 35:31.995
As hard as we worked
on this brilliant thing,

35:31.997 --> 35:33.396
if it don't work,

35:33.398 --> 35:35.465
we've wasted a lot of time.

35:35.467 --> 35:37.567
-Yeah.
-[ramsey] and several dollars.

35:38.670 --> 35:40.804
<i>  The damn storm's a-coming.</i>

35:40.806 --> 35:42.672
<i> [digger] if they don't</i>
<i>  move, we're done.</i>

35:48.981 --> 35:50.213
<i> [digger] get in there, boy.</i>

35:50.215 --> 35:51.882
You're under arrest.

35:51.884 --> 35:54.050
<i> [ramsey] oh, I don't</i>
<i>  put no liquor in here.</i>

35:54.052 --> 35:55.018
<i>  Damn, jail house.</i>

35:55.020 --> 35:56.620
[digger] damn, brother,
what you do?

35:57.322 --> 35:58.989
They cut your hand off.

35:59.324 --> 36:00.924
This ain't no count.

36:00.926 --> 36:03.660
Well, I'll be here to see
you in the morning.

36:03.662 --> 36:06.029
I'll be right over here on
this flea ridden bed,

36:06.031 --> 36:08.298
taking me a nap,
waiting on you.

36:08.300 --> 36:10.267
Don't you dare try to escape.

36:10.269 --> 36:12.102
[ramsey chuckles]
so, that was a bust.

36:12.104 --> 36:13.470
[digger] as usual.

36:16.909 --> 36:18.808
<i> [ramsey] the damn</i>
<i>  storm's a-coming.</i>

36:18.810 --> 36:20.911
<i> [digger] if they don't</i>
<i>  move, we're done.</i>

36:20.913 --> 36:22.479
<i> [digger] whether this</i>
<i>  is gonna work or not,</i>

36:22.481 --> 36:23.980
it remains to be seen

36:23.982 --> 36:26.917
but at this point, it's all we
got, it's our only option.

36:29.655 --> 36:32.055
Here we go, here
it comes, guys.

36:32.057 --> 36:33.757
<i> [digger] there you go,</i>
<i>  there's your guest coming.</i>

36:33.759 --> 36:35.225
We're catching wind, guys.

36:35.227 --> 36:37.527
[digger] yeah, if we just get
a little bit more wind.

36:37.529 --> 36:39.429
<i> [ramsey] little bit more,</i>
<i>  it's a-coming.</i>

36:43.368 --> 36:44.734
[digger] oh, yeah.

36:44.736 --> 36:47.404
Hell yeah. Look how
it's blowing here.

36:47.406 --> 36:49.372
[ramsey] that's the plan,
that's all we gotta do.

36:49.374 --> 36:51.274
[digger] oh, it's gotta
move, right there.

36:51.276 --> 36:53.810
This ain't out of control
wind and it's a-moving.

36:53.812 --> 36:56.313
Yes, this is just a good,
steady breeze.

36:56.315 --> 36:58.915
[ramsey] if it'll do this two
or three days a week,

36:58.917 --> 37:00.383
we're golden, boys.

37:00.385 --> 37:02.385
You know, as long as
these old chariots here

37:02.387 --> 37:04.020
are moving a little bit,

37:04.022 --> 37:05.889
<i>  then the whisky</i>
<i>  inside the barrel</i>

37:05.891 --> 37:07.958
<i>  don't have any</i>
<i>  choice but to move.</i>

37:07.960 --> 37:09.459
Just like a baby in a cradle.

37:09.461 --> 37:12.062
It's as safe as it was
in its mommy's arms.

37:12.064 --> 37:13.730
Thing about it is,
when these stop,

37:13.732 --> 37:14.965
that liquor ain't stopped,

37:14.967 --> 37:17.400
it's still in there moving,
it's sloshing around.

37:17.402 --> 37:20.036
We got the biometric
pressure changes here,

37:20.038 --> 37:21.538
we got the temperature changes

37:21.540 --> 37:23.340
<i>  and now we've got the wind.</i>

37:23.342 --> 37:24.407
All this is perfect.

37:24.409 --> 37:26.009
We couldn't have
got it no better.

37:26.011 --> 37:28.078
God, we've done
it sure as hell.

37:28.080 --> 37:29.879
<i> All the hard work is paid off,</i>

37:29.881 --> 37:31.248
it is gonna work.

37:31.250 --> 37:33.917
<i>  I'll tell you one thing,</i>
<i>  I was concerned.</i>

37:33.919 --> 37:35.785
You know, we've
worked terribly hard

37:35.787 --> 37:37.020
to get this done.

37:37.022 --> 37:39.422
I was pretty much ready
to throw in the towel on it.

37:39.424 --> 37:41.758
[digger] I'd hate to have done
all of that damn work

37:41.760 --> 37:43.260
-for nothing, wouldn't you?
-[ramsey] yeah.

37:43.262 --> 37:45.028
<i>  I think all of our hard</i>
<i>  work has paid off,</i>

37:45.030 --> 37:46.196
it's gonna work fine.

37:46.198 --> 37:47.931
That's why they say, if you
don't like the weather

37:47.933 --> 37:49.299
in the mountains,
wait a few minutes.

37:49.301 --> 37:50.734
[digger] wait a few
minutes, it will change.

37:50.736 --> 37:51.768
I'm liking it.

37:51.770 --> 37:54.904
I'd like it even more when
about six months pass.

37:54.906 --> 37:57.374
<i>  This is gonna revolutionize</i>
<i>  our liquor selling world,</i>

37:57.376 --> 37:58.975
we're gonna get
five-year old liquor

37:58.977 --> 38:00.410
in five to six months.

38:00.412 --> 38:02.345
Longer it stays in there,
better it's gonna get.

38:02.347 --> 38:03.346
Exactly.

38:03.348 --> 38:05.815
I say, we just come
and get it as we need it.

38:05.817 --> 38:06.883
[digger] oh, yeah.
There ain't no sense

38:06.885 --> 38:08.051
in taking 'em all out at once.

38:08.053 --> 38:11.288
Whenever we get one, we
just replace it with another.

38:11.290 --> 38:14.124
Yeah. Daniel, you know what
this means, don't you?

38:14.126 --> 38:16.059
You and kelly's gotta
double time it now,

38:16.061 --> 38:18.094
we gotta step up our
tennessee whisky.

38:18.096 --> 38:19.362
We gotta have them
tennessee whisky.

38:19.364 --> 38:20.997
<i>  This old dream catcher here</i>

38:20.999 --> 38:22.966
seems to be what
dreams are made of.

38:22.968 --> 38:24.868
Boys, we ain't doing
it no justice here.

38:24.870 --> 38:27.504
A watched pot don't boil
and watched liquor don't age.

38:27.506 --> 38:31.074
<i>  I think, dream catcher whisky</i>
<i>  has a right, catchy sound.</i>

38:31.076 --> 38:32.809
This calls for celebration.

38:32.811 --> 38:34.244
You know, I'd probably try it.

38:34.246 --> 38:37.113
<i>  Sea aging in the mountains.</i>

38:45.257 --> 38:47.891
<i> [mike] the champagne went over</i>
<i>  really well at the wedding.</i>

38:47.893 --> 38:50.093
<i>  I'm gonna see</i>
<i>  this guy, biscuit.</i>

38:50.095 --> 38:52.996
A friend of mine, o'brien,
put me onto him.

38:52.998 --> 38:54.230
It's his cousin.

38:54.232 --> 38:55.965
I'm gonna go up there
and see if he wants to buy

38:55.967 --> 38:57.667
the rest of this stuff.

38:57.669 --> 38:59.069
He sounded really interested,

38:59.071 --> 39:01.504
I'm bringing the rest
of the 24 bottles.

39:01.506 --> 39:03.273
<i>  I'm gonna try to drag</i>
<i>  a pretty damn good,</i>

39:03.275 --> 39:04.441
<i>  hard bargain tonight.</i>

39:04.443 --> 39:06.042
<i>  I'm gonna try to get</i>
<i>  a 100 bucks</i>

39:06.044 --> 39:07.744
<i>  a damn bottle for this stuff.</i>

39:07.746 --> 39:09.279
And try to get some
money in my pocket

39:09.281 --> 39:11.081
to give back to jerry
to help him with his,

39:11.083 --> 39:13.216
you know, hospital bills.

39:13.218 --> 39:15.251
<i>  It's been a few days</i>
<i>  since my wedding now</i>

39:15.253 --> 39:17.354
<i>  and... All I can think about</i>

39:17.356 --> 39:19.022
is trying to help jerry out

39:19.024 --> 39:21.891
with his financial state and
his doctor bills and stuff.

39:21.893 --> 39:24.260
I'm gonna see if I can't
sell some champagne.

39:25.497 --> 39:27.230
<i>  I just wanna get</i>
<i>  this stuff sold</i>

39:27.232 --> 39:29.032
<i>  for a damn good premium price</i>

39:29.034 --> 39:31.835
and get some money
back in jerry's pocket.

39:31.837 --> 39:33.670
-[biscuit] hey, there!
-What's going on?

39:33.672 --> 39:36.139
-[biscuit] mike, right?
-Yup, you must be biscuit.

39:36.141 --> 39:37.874
That's right, that's me,
how are you doing?

39:37.876 --> 39:39.409
[mike] all right, nice
to meet you, brother.

39:39.911 --> 39:41.378
Well, I heard from o'brien

39:41.380 --> 39:44.280
that you might want some
of this champagne here.

39:44.282 --> 39:45.949
Well, o'brien said
it was really good.

39:45.951 --> 39:48.151
He was just raving about it.

39:48.153 --> 39:49.819
It had really good
flavor and everything.

39:49.821 --> 39:52.122
[mike] it does, it's got
a damn good flavor.

39:53.959 --> 39:55.191
You wanna take a sip of it?

39:55.193 --> 39:57.127
[biscuit] yeah, let me see
what it tastes like.

39:57.562 --> 39:58.561
He said it was really--

40:00.065 --> 40:01.064
[mike] whoa!

40:02.134 --> 40:03.533
Well, that's gonna take off,
ain't it?

40:04.302 --> 40:05.235
[mike] yeah, buddy!

40:05.237 --> 40:07.203
-Ooh, buddy.
-[mike] it's champagne.

40:07.205 --> 40:09.172
That's good champagne,
right there.

40:09.674 --> 40:11.941
Well, it smells good.

40:11.943 --> 40:14.043
Some of the backwoods finest
blueberry champagne.

40:14.045 --> 40:15.311
[biscuit] you can
smell blueberry in it.

40:15.313 --> 40:17.380
[mike] take you a little sip
and see what you think.

40:21.386 --> 40:23.787
O'brien was right, that's got
the flavors coming right out
in it.

40:23.789 --> 40:25.255
-[mike] you like it?
-That is really good.

40:25.257 --> 40:28.458
He loves it. I can see it
in his eyes, he's wanting it.

40:28.460 --> 40:29.926
I'll tell you what,

40:29.928 --> 40:31.494
it's gonna cost you
$100 a bottle.

40:31.496 --> 40:33.096
Oh, man!

40:33.098 --> 40:34.330
Coming at me hard, ain't you?

40:34.332 --> 40:35.865
[mike] well, what
are you thinking?

40:35.867 --> 40:38.268
-I was think $50 a bottle.
-[mike] oh! [bleep]

40:38.270 --> 40:39.436
you're crazier than hell.

40:39.438 --> 40:41.037
I gotta make money on it.

40:41.706 --> 40:44.073
I don't do this stuff
for my health.

40:44.075 --> 40:46.676
I'll tell you what I do,
I go $90 a bottle on it

40:46.678 --> 40:49.979
and, you know, that's gonna
be about it, man, for me.

40:50.215 --> 40:52.649
I can't go that high.

40:53.485 --> 40:55.385
I'll take all 24
of 'em, right now,

40:55.387 --> 40:57.654
if you give me $75 a bottle.

40:57.656 --> 40:59.189
That's as high as I can go.

41:00.959 --> 41:03.359
$75, I see.

41:05.197 --> 41:07.197
-That sounds like a deal.
-That will work.

41:07.199 --> 41:10.066
You know, that's $1,800
going straight to jerry.

41:10.068 --> 41:11.734
I sold each and every bottle.

41:11.736 --> 41:13.303
This is a heavy load.

41:13.305 --> 41:15.338
-[biscuit] just set
it right there.
-[mike] yes, sir.

41:15.340 --> 41:16.973
You know, all that
matters to me

41:16.975 --> 41:18.708
is getting jerry
back to full health

41:18.710 --> 41:21.044
and giving him the money
to pay his bills

41:21.046 --> 41:22.979
<i>  and getting him back</i>
<i>  in the field with me.</i>

41:22.981 --> 41:24.314
[biscuit] I appreciate
you, brother.

41:24.316 --> 41:26.216
[mike] all right, man.
You have a good one.

41:26.218 --> 41:27.317
[biscuit] all right,
man. You too.
